Job Title: Data Scientist (Mid-Level)
Location: Lahore, Pakistan
Company: Nova Analytics Pvt. Ltd.
Department: Data Science & AI
Employment Type: Full-Time
Reports To: Lead Data Scientist

About the Company
At Nova Analytics, we help businesses unlock the true potential of their data. From predictive analytics to AI-driven solutions, our mission is to empower clients with insights that drive meaningful decisions. We are currently seeking a mid-level Data Scientist to join our expanding team of data professionals in Lahore.

Role Summary
As a Mid-Level Data Scientist, you will design, develop, and deploy machine learning models and data solutions to solve complex business problems. You’ll work on diverse projects involving large-scale data, predictive modeling, natural language processing, and data visualization, collaborating with cross-functional teams to deliver actionable intelligence.

Key Responsibilities
Work on end-to-end machine learning projects: data collection, preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and deployment

Analyze large datasets to extract meaningful insights and trends

Build predictive and classification models using libraries such as scikit-learn, XGBoost, TensorFlow, or PyTorch

Implement data pipelines using tools like Python, SQL, and Airflow

Conduct A/B testing and statistical analysis to validate hypotheses

Present results to stakeholders through clear visualizations and written reports

Collaborate with data engineers, analysts, and domain experts to ensure data quality and usability

Continuously monitor and improve the performance of deployed models

Required Qualifications
Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Data Science, Computer Science, Statistics, or a related field

2–4 years of hands-on experience in data science or machine learning roles

Proficient in Python and SQL

Solid understanding of statistics, probability, and data structures

Experience with machine learning libraries (e.g., scikit-learn, pandas, NumPy, TensorFlow, PyTorch)

Familiarity with version control (e.g., Git) and data visualization tools (e.g., Matplotlib, Seaborn, Power BI)

Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to explain complex results in simple terms

Preferred Qualifications
Experience with cloud platforms such as AWS, GCP, or Azure

Exposure to NLP, time-series forecasting, or deep learning

Experience in deploying models with Docker, FastAPI, or Flask

Familiarity with MLOps tools such as MLflow or DVC

Contributions to open-source or published data science projects

What We Offer
Competitive salary and annual bonus

Health insurance for self and immediate family

Paid leaves, flexible working hours, and hybrid work policy

Access to online learning resources and training sessions

A collaborative work culture that values innovation, curiosity, and growth

How to Apply
Send your updated CV and portfolio (if available) to careers@novaanalytics.pk with the subject line: Data Scientist – Mid-Level Application. Mention relevant projects and GitHub/LinkedIn profiles if applicable.
